    described the app as X11-only.

 -- Md Salman Siddik <salmansiddik19@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 15:05:00 +0600

meeting-recorder (0.2.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add Wayland screen capture via the xdg-desktop-portal ScreenCast API.
    X11 sessions keep using x11grab; the backend is chosen automatically.
    Because ffmpeg has no PipeWire input device, a gst-launch-1.0 pipewiresrc
    pump feeds raw frames into the same ffmpeg process that records the audio,
    so A/V stay on one clock and pause/resume is unchanged.
  * The screen-sharing permission is requested once and remembered; denying it
    (or an unresponsive portal) now records audio only instead of failing.
  * Fix finalize discarding a whole recording when no video was captured: it
    mapped a video stream that the segments did not contain.
  * Fix `meeting-recorder record` having no tray icon, timer or pause/resume,
    and show the controls as soon as Record is pressed rather than once capture
    starts.
  * Stop amplifying background noise: loudnorm ran after denoising and lifted
    room tone with the voice. A gate now runs before it.
  * Reduce notifications to the Record/Ignore prompt and the saved result.
  * Depend on xdg-desktop-portal and the GStreamer PipeWire plugins; x11-utils
    and x11-xserver-utils move to Recommends.

 -- Md Salman Siddik <salmansiddik19@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:45:00 +0600

meeting-recorder (0.1.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix `meeting-recorder record` never producing a final file: the manual
    record command now waits for the background finalize pass (concat +
    denoise + loudness normalize) instead of exiting immediately, which had
    left orphaned .partN segments and no output .mkv.

